<TEXT>
cornelius p turner developer of the 
general educational development tests that permit nongraduates to 
win certificates equivalent to a high school diploma is dead at 
83 
turner died of blood poisoning at alexandria hospital on 
wednesday he lived in alexandria 
as a navy lieutenant from 1943 to 1945 turner directed a 
program that developed highschool diploma equivalency tests for 
use by members of the armed services during world war ii 
after the war he held a number of positions that helped expand 
use of the tests until all us states and canadian provinces 
adopted them about 700000 people a year take the tests 
he taught mathematics and history at leicester mass and served 
as superintendent of schools there before world war ii 
turner is survived by a son and two grandchildren his wife of 
53 years mary died in 1987 
