iraq although irans foreign ministry claimed no knowledge of the 
deal 
but experts say saddam cannot rely on airlifts to feed his 
nation of 17 million people nor will his order this week to 
farmers to devote 80 percent of their land to wheat help much 
according to us agriculture department officials 
