8 percent continuing a sixyear moderating trend according to the 
annual college board survey released wednesday 
but with a possible recession and resurgent inflation some 
college officials fear tuition may climb more sharply in the next 
few years 
the survey found that fixed charges at fouryear private 
institutions including tuition fees room and board average 
13544 an 8 percent increase from last years 12557 the 
increase a year ago was 9 percent 
the priciest such school mit costs an estimated 22945 
counting tuition fees room and board books and supplies 
transportation and other expenses 
bennington a small selective liberal arts college had been 
the most expensive private college every year since the 198586 
school year mit was tops for the three years before that 
