pizza hut is trying to swallow a big slice of 
moscow bureaucracy battling to keep its two new restaurants open 
after health inspectors shut them a company official says 
restaurant officials say the inspectors are unfamiliar with 
modern technology such as automatic dishwashers or western ways of 
preparing restaurant food and that its just a simple 
misunderstanding 
the pizzerias part of a 10 million joint venture between 
pepsico incs european branch and the moscow city restaurant 
department opened sept 11 and feature americanstyle pizzas 
garlic bread and salad bars for both dollars and rubles 
since they opened soviets have waited in long lines to dine at 
the redandwhite checkered tables amid brass railings and fake 
tropical plants 
on sept 20 however the larger of the two pizza huts on 
