the decision wednesday against southern management corp of 
silver spring md was the first court test of a fair housing law 
barring discrimination against handicapped individuals officials 
said 
since the law went into effect in march 1989 the justice 
department has defined handicapped to include recovering 
substance abusers an interpretation upheld by us district judge 
albert v bryan jr 
