prime minister toshiki kaifu unveiled a plan today 
to dispatch japanese military personnel overseas for the first time 
since world war ii but he said they would be unarmed and kept away 
from combat 
the proposal which must be approved by the parliament calls 
for the establishment of the un peace cooperation corps a group 
of military and civilian personnel to participate in un 
peacekeeping activities 
