and a foreign ministry spokesman in paris called the threat 
utterly intolerable he said france would consult with other 
countries facing the same threat 
the note said that giving sanctuary to a foreigner was 
espionage and iraq would execute anyone commiting such a crime 
the iraqi foreign ministry refused to elaborate on the message 
today but iraqi officials said it was referring to iraqis 
harboring westerners not to diplomats giving westerners refuge 
the iraqi officials speaking on condition of anonymity said 
the memo only contained a reminder of an iraqi law issued when 
iraq annexed kuwait last month which stipulated that those who 
provide refuge for foreigners could be punished by death the 
officials said the law applies only to iraqis 
on wednesday baker called the iraqi threat repugnant and 
rejected a demand for the names of people given sanctuary in the 
us embassies in baghdad and kuwait 
the foreign office spokesman who spoke on condition of 
anonymity said britain regarded the note as a threat to kill its 
diplomats we have no option but to regard this as such a 
threat said the spokesman 
