owners they have demanded tax hikes for the rich as a tradeoff 
administration bargainers offered to leave the capital gains tax 
rate at current levels in exchange for exempting the increased 
value of assets due to inflation said officials who asked not to 
be identified 
i think its still a very viable option said one republican 
official 
democrats brushed aside the idea one official said but there 
were other signs of a new white house flexibility on the issue 
republican lawmakers who met with bush at the white house early 
wednesday said that rather on insisting on a capital gains tax cut 
the president was demanding a package with items intended to spur 
economic growth these might include tax breaks for companies that 
conduct research or do business in deteriorating cities or rural 
areas the republicans said 
a number of options have come up foley said during a break 
in the closeddoor budget talks but whether they can be called a 
true alternative to a capital gains tax cut is debatable 
the two top republicans in congress michel and senate minority 
leader bob dole rkan have already said a reduction in the 
capital gains tax rate should not be an absolute demand at the 
negotiations 
bargainers racing to hammer out a deal faced a dwindling number 
of days in which to act with congress planning to recess from 
friday afternoon through saturday for the jewish holiday of yom 
kippur a fullfledged sunday session seemed likely 
the house was ready to vote on a bill temporarily financing the 
