<TEXT>
king edward viii who abdicated in 1936 to marry 
an american divorcee lied about the size of his fortune pleading 
poverty to secure a royal income before going into exile his first 
official biography said thursday 
author philip ziegler has written king edward viii the 
official biography with the approval of queen elizabeth ii 
edwards niece 
working from the archives of buckingham palace and government 
papers ziegler reveals that edward told a meeting of his family 
and their advisers that his income would hardly be 22500 a year 
and that his total fortune was 405000 
as a result he was guaranteed a yearly income of 94500 on 
condition that he went abroad and would not return without 
government consent he immediately left for france taking the 
title duke of windsor 
ulick alexander keeper of the privy purse later calculated 
that edwards fortune amounted to nearly 5 million excluding real 
estate in canada the sum would be equivalent to 43 million at 
presentday values 
when this was told to king george vi who had succeeded his 
brother on the throne he wrote to edward three months after the 
abdication you were under great strain and i am not seeking to 
reproach you or anyone but the fact remains that i was badly 
misled 
ziegler says the financial arrangements for edwards future did 
more than anything else to poison the atmosphere between him and 
