force later in the crisis said rep lee hamilton dind 
rep william broomfield rmich fumed that it was amazing 
that we can get approval through the united nations for the 
presidents actions but not through the congress i think its 
unfortunate that we cant even get approval when weve got 80 
percent of the american people behind the president 
the administration has decided to divide the saudi arms package 
into two parts one to meet immediate saudi defense needs in the 
current crisis including weapons that can be delivered from 
current stocks or quickly taken off the production line and a 
second 14 billion package to be proposed in january to meet the 
countrys longerterm needs 
the latter package will include f15f fighter planes and more 
tanks said the sources who spoke on condition of anonymity the 
delay will give lawmakers more time to deliberate how the sale 
might change the military balance in the volatile region levine 
said 
at the same time the administration has been discussing a new 
package of military aid to israel and senior officials have 
promised to maintain israels qualitative military advantage over 
neighboring states 
in deliberations a day earlier two foreign affairs subcommittees 
sought to make it clear their support for bushs moves so far did 
not imply authorization for future military action 
we have no interest in providing conditional authority to the 
president with regard to future military actions committee 
chairman dante fascell dfla said during a meeting of the middle 
east and arms control subcommittees on wednesday 
we will deal with that judge that as the american people 
will if and when that time arrives fascell said 
action by the full committee would culminate a weeklong 
internal debate between lawmakers who believe congress should take 
a formal part in the gulf situation and those who prefer to keep 
their political distance from it similar talks are under way in 
the senate 
i think its important for congress to act here said 
hamilton chairman of the middle east subcommittee i know some 
of our colleagues would prefer not to take any action but this is 
one of the most significant foreign policy moves in a long 
time i would be uncomfortable if we ignored it 
the resolution condemns the invasion of kuwait and supports 
bushs diplomatic efforts and use of the united nations to bring 
international pressure on iraq to leave kuwait and release 
hostages 
the united states shall to the extent possible use 
diplomatic and other nonmilitary means in order to achieve those 
objectives and policies while maintaining credible united states 
and multinational deterrent military force the resolution says 
fascell said he does not consider the resolution to trigger the 
war powers act which would start the clock running on a 60day 
limit to the us troop deployment he said bush has consulted well 
with congress and met the objectives of the war powers act and a 
confrontation with the white house over the laws technicalities 
would not be useful 
the resolution also calls for continued international efforts to 
contain iraqs military might including proliferation of ballistic 
missiles and weapons of mass destruction and reaffirms the us 
policy of maintaining israels qualitative military edge over its 
neighbors 
