the senate judiciary committee voted 131 
today to approve president bushs nomination of judge david souter 
to the supreme court 
the panel sent its recommendation to the full senate where 
confirmation was expected within a few days republicans urged a 
speedy vote so souter could take his seat before the court opens 
its term on monday 
sen edward m kennedy dmass cast the only vote against 
souter 
souter did not attend the committee session he remained in new 
hampshire listening to the proceedings from a radio in the law 
office of his close friend former state attorney general tom rath 
souter issued a statement several hours after the vote thanking 
members of the committee for their courtesy and consideration 
and said i am gratified by their action i await the decision of 
the full senate 
committee chairman joseph biden ddel joined with six other 
committee democrats and all six republicans in supporting souter 
like many of his democratic colleagues biden said he was troubled 
by uncertainty surrounding souters positions on rights issues 
including abortion 
hes about the best though that were going to be able to do 
from this administration biden said 
president bush in cleveland to campaign for republican 
candidates said the committee vote is good news for all of us 
who are committed to the constitution of the united states hell 
be a superb justice for the supreme court 
he urged the full senate to act as quickly as possible to 
confirm this man so that he could be seated when the court opens 
its session next week 
