operation that the fec found in violation of limits on party 
contributions said bob bauer general counsel for the democratic 
senatorial campaign committee 
republicans defend the inner circle as a legitimate joint 
fundraising operation exempt from the contribution limits 
federal law allows party committees to give candidates 17500 
and spend an additional amount on their behalf according to 
individual state populations 
a federal judge last year ruled in a lawsuit filed by common 
cause that the national republican senatorial committee illegally 
funneled 27 million in individual contributions to a dozen 1986 
senate candidates through a maneuver known as bundling the fec 
has asked the court to fine the nrsc as much as 27 million 
the differences between the 1986 and 1990 operations are no 
more than cosmetic the democrats said in a complaint filed with 
the fec 
the inner circle cannot qualify as a joint fundraising 
operation if nrsc controls where the money goes provides the staff 
and receives just 1 percent of the money it raises the complaint 
said 
