hoped to retrieve the other half of the door by the end of the 
week 
the board said the navy submarine sea cliff videotaped the piece 
of the airplane on the ocean floor and raised it to the surface 
with hydraulic jaws it was brought onto the deck of the navy 
vessel the laney choust at about 5 am edt today midnight 
honolulu time 
the safety board said a preliminary examination by one of its 
investigators showed the door had fractured longitudinally near the 
midspan latch the eight sectors of the latch lock were all in the 
locked position and were deformed 
the board said the sea cliff had also detected a strong sonar 
target near the spot where the door portion was found it said the 
submarine would return to try to locate the remainder of the door 
after being recharged for about 20 hours 
after investigators examine the recovered debris parts of it 
will be sent to boeing in seattle for a more detailed review under 
board direction officials said 
the door flew off after united airlines flight 811 experienced 
an explosive decompression at about 23000 feet 
