the irancontra special prosecutor indicated 
thursday that he may seek more indictments but expressed 
determination to conclude the investigation by next spring 
independent counsel lawrence e walsh said his office is 
reviewing recently obtained records of the irancontra affair and 
questioning previously unavailable witnesses as prosecutors work to 
conclude the nearly fouryearold investigation 
in remarks prepared for delivery thursday in topeka kan walsh 
said he would not make a decision about closing down his office 
until after an appeals court reviews the convictions of former 
national security adviser john m poindexter 
poindexter is appealing his sixmonth sentence for obstructing 
congressional inquiries about covert military aid to nicaraguan 
rebels and the sale of arms to iran a decision on poindexters 
appeal of five felony convictions is not expected until spring 
ideally the work of the office except for possible appeals 
and the trial of any outstanding indictments should be concluded 
after this decision walsh said 
during the intervening months our investigation should be 
completed walsh said in the speech at washburn university 
walshs remarks indicated that his original timetable for 
closing down the investigation had slipped at least six more 
months 
following poindexters conviction in april walsh said he hoped 
to decide by this fall on whether to conclude the investigation 
since his appointment in late 1986 walsh has obtained eight 
convictions of irancontra figures including poindexter and former 
