congress approved a bill thursday offering 
money and an apology to the socalled victims of the cold war 
in some western states who may have developed cancer from nuclear 
bomb testing or uranium mining 
the bill approved on voice vote by the house and sent to the 
president is an admission that the government was wrong to test 
nuclear weapons above ground in nevada while people were living in 
fallout areas downwind said rep barney frank dmass who led 
debate for the measure 
