compensatory payment of a small amount he said 
aboveground nuclear tests throw radioactive debris into the 
atmosphere that can settle far away from the explosion site a 
major source of radioactivity in such cases was an isotope of 
strontium which was eaten by cows in their pastures passed on in 
their milk and taken up in human bones like calcium 
the united states and the soviet union agreed to stop testing 
above ground in 1963 
the radioactive decay of uranium releases radon a radioactive 
gas that can build up in mines it was the increase of lung cancer 
among miners that alerted public health authorities to the dangers 
of radon buildup in homes usually to much lower concentrations 
than in mines 
