two quakes measuring 43 and 
47 on the richter scale shook central south africa early thursday 
killing two miners working more than a mile underground 
five other miners at the president brand gold mine southwest of 
johannesburg suffered minor injuries officials said 
the tremors hit seconds apart before dawn in the orange free 
state and western transvaal areas according to news reports 
cracks in buildings and other minor damage were reported in welkom 
about 125 miles southwest of johannesburg 
mine officials said they would investigate the deaths and 
injuries in a shaft 13 miles beneath the surface 
south africas gold mines are the deepest in the world 
accidents claim dozens of lifes in the mines each year 
a quake of magnitude 4 is capable of causing moderate damage 
while one of magnitude 5 can cause considerable damage 
