industry executives last spring 
it was supplier relations of consoritum members not the austin 
texasbased consortium itself that drew criticism 
the gao report said the suppliers want the consortium members to 
emulate sematechs example in working more closely with them 
the gao interviewers found that half their subjects said 
sematechs member companies need to establish better relationships 
with them 
the suppliers particularly wanted longterm relationships 
permitting them to participate in their customers planning to 
share technical performance data and to get their customers to 
assume some of the costs and risks associated with developing the 
next generation of equipment 
three suppliers noted japanese companies provide better 
feedback than their us counterparts on how their equipment is 
performing 
