it has not been a quiet week in twin peaks the 
enigmatic little lumber town in the pacific northwest where the 
women are strange the men are oddlooking and the children are 
all above suspicion 
lake woebegon it aint twin peaks is not a place its a 
state of mind to which millions of americans will return sunday 
night for the season premiere of televisions oddest nighttime 
drama 
after eight episodes just seven days in twin peaks time we 
still dont know who killed laura palmer the homecoming queen 
whose plasticwrapped corpse fuels the series central mystery she 
is still dead maybe 
then theres wacky cherry piegobbling fbi agent dale cooper 
kyle maclachlan he has declared he knows the killers identity 
but in the season finale was laid low by an unknown assailant and 
three gunshots to the chest 
theres more one suspect in lauras killing has been smothered 
by her father another has been shot theres been a heart attack 
a drug overdose a lifethreatening fire and a brothelkeeper has 
unknowingly hired his own daughter 
as actor michael ontkean twin peaks doughty sheriff harry s 
truman observed the series is a kabukistyle peyton place on 
peyote buttons 
abc says little about the twohour special abc sunday night 
movie directed by david lynch and written by mark frost 
cocreators of the series 
the investigation into the mysterious killing continues 
sorrow settles over the community as several lives hang in the 
balance abc said audrey horne finds herself a terrified 
prisoner and donna hayward receives a strange message 
this is a strange time for a strange series 
it was conceived by lynch the high priest of cinematic anxiety 
eraserhead the elephant man dune blue velvet 
and wild at heart and frost an established tv producer from 
hill street blues 
a midseason replacement twin peaks was the years most 
writtenabout show even before its april 8 debut won a 33 percent 
share of the tv audience it quickly became the most talkedabout 
show on television 
were just trying to reimagine the genre of the nighttime 
soap in the way that hill street blues did the cop show a decade 
ago frost said but it was much more than that 
viewers got a sense of place in twin peaks its geography and 
exteriors provided by the lovely town of snoqualmie wash the town 
was as placid as a forest pond where every droplet teems with 
violent microscopic life 
the critics loved the shows dreamlike allusive imagery the 
dazzling cinematography of ron garcia and the ethereal score of 
composer angelo badalamenti 
most of all they loved the townspeople mordantly eccentric 
characters whose plots and subplots were cryptic to the point of 
inscrutability 
every conversation had meaning every gesture was freighted with 
hidden significance every scene charged with a sense that 
something dreadful was about to happen the tension wasnt 
relieved only punctuated by black comedy 
there had never been anything like it on television 
even film critic pauline kael of the new yorker magazine was 
hooked it has both the insidious weirdness of of lynchs best 
movie work and the weird insidiousness of topoftheline tv trash 
lynch sets us drifting through a vivid dream of american 
life 
the new york times adored twin peaks dont miss it 
said one review its editorial page ventured that the series has 
been hailed as revolutionary tv it has become in any case a 
phenomenon heady stuff that 
i killed laura palmer tshirts appeared food writers 
devoted columns to cherry pie on fridays the shows ardent fans 
would gather to analyze every clue and argue over meanings 
computer enthusiasts would bicker about the show on electronic 
bulletin boards ordinarily sensible people who wouldnt admit to 
watching thirtysomething became instant babbling fans 
hailed as the television show of the 90s twin peaks was 
everything except a hit 
its opening audience share of 33 percent quickly slumped when 
twin peaks went to its regular time slot thursday nights 
against nbcs blockbuster cheers twin peaks gradually lost 
about half of its viewers 
the season finale won its time period with a 126 rating and a 
22 share or about 97 million viewers a ratings point represented 
921000 tv households a share the percentage of all tv sets in use 
tuned to a given show 
it finished the season with a respectable if unspectacular tie 
for 40th place but abc already had decided to renew the show on 
oct 6 it moves to saturday night with china beach the 
critically acclaimed vietnam war series 
abc says both shows attract adult viewers ages 18 to 49 a 
demographic group prized by advertisers about 40 million of whom 
tune in on saturday nights abcs secret fear is that twin 
peaks will lose to rented videos 
twin peaks fared poorly in the annual emmy awards despite 
its 14 nominations the most of any drama it won only two 
technical awards 
daily variety the trade journal blamed that on critics who 
may actually have done it a disservice attaching expectations to 
it that it will be hardpressed to meet 
 
