<TEXT>
is michael milken the selfless quiet 
conservative religious civicminded philanthropic father 
husband and family man he is depicted in letters to the judge who 
will sentence him 
or is he the greedy powerseeking conspiratorial corrupt 
confessed criminal who systematically and fraudulently engaged in 
illegal payoffs and other acts to gain a fabulous income as 
depicted by prosecutors 
hundreds of letters in support of milken have been received by 
judge kimba wood leading a reader to wonder if michael milken is 
possessed of two utterly disparate personalities 
that is only the beginning of the questions provoked by the 
letters all written in an effort to convince wood that milken 
should be sentenced to less than the maximum term of 28 years and 
instead be ordered to assist in community projects 
the letters whch describe a private person so unlike the 
public image of milken the confessed criminal provide an unusual 
psychological case study of human behavior and perception 
there are letters from attorneys for instance that emphasize 
milkens personal values and contain nothing whatever about legal 
issues 
there is praise from beneficiaries of milkens charities 
without reference to the possibility that the funds assigned to 
them were obtained illegally 
there are business people suggesting that milkens values are so 
unlike and higher than those of so many business people 
and there are educators who tell of how milken by his personal 
example and effort is a positive influence on the education of 
children 
daryl gates los angeles police chief says he pursues a hard 
line against criminals he suggests the court could consider 
milkens financial expertise in arriving at a productive rather 
than solely punitive sentence 
los angeles archbishop roger mahony observes that his schools 
seek to instill decent values in the lives of young students he 
asks that milken be sentenced to enhanced community service 
rather than punished by jail 
richard adler is a judge of the california superior court but 
his letter to judge wood refers only to milkens character and his 
ability as a mathematics teacher including personal help he gave 
to the judges son 
steven j ross chairman of timewarner inc is widely known as 
a sharp nononsense harddriving businessman he writes that 
milken is no ivan boesky or martin siegel no gordon gekko no 
yuppie no wheeler and dealer 
instead he says milken is a person of ideas and ideals 
and strangely immaterialistic a longterm thinker not a 
quickbuck artist a man who sometimes put client financial 
interests ahead of his own 
the letters are almost invariably long far longer rambling 
repetitive and anecdotal than ordinary business letters but 
otherwise unsually well presented ross letter is five typwritten 
pages but others are twice that length 
almost all writers comment positively on an aspect of milkens 
personality and way of life his loyalty concern love of 
children quiet family life religious commitment honesty or 
devotion to people and causes 
themes reappearing throughout the file of letters are that bad 
things happen to good people that the tragedy of human frailty can 
destroy otherwise strong human beings and the belief that good 
deeds should mitigate penalties 
whatever is made of the letters now is likely to be magnified 
and examined in detail after the sentence is pronounced and one 
question that will be asked over and over is whether the support of 
the big would ever be so available to the small 
</TEXT>
