<TEXT>
in the 200th year since the birth of the first 
amendment the winds of censorship are gusting stronger than ever 
this could be called the year of the censor 
federal support of arts projects deemed obscene has been 
threatened record store owners face fines and possible arrest for 
selling lps containing lyrics or artwork dubbed obscene a rash of 
movies have been slapped with the dreaded x rating and a museum is 
going on trial for obscenity an american first 
already the film industry is adjusting the x rating was 
eliminated wednesday by the motion picture association of america 
which substituted a new nc17 rating that bars children altogether 
but does not carry the stigma of the x 
throughout the history of the united states censorship in one 
form or another political religious moral or military has 
stalked literature dance opera film music and art 
this the land of the fruited plain home of the brave and 
citadel of free speech banned walt whitmans leaves of grass 
took the wiggle out of mae wests walk cut the moaning from ray 
charles whatd i say burned james joyces ulysses put 
lenny bruce in jail and kept isadora duncan from dancing 
now the contemporary arts center in cincinnati and its director 
dennis barrie face misdemeanor charges of pandering obscenity and 
displaying nude photos of children in an exhibit of photographer 
robert mapplethorpe a homosexual who died of aids last year jury 
selection in a county court began last week 
a mapplethorpe exhibit last june at the corcoran gallery of art 
in washington was canceled after sen jesse helms rnc declared 
some of the artists photographs to be obscene helms objections 
resulted in a move by congress to limit federal funds to the arts 
i wasnt starting out to make a statement that isnt the way 
i work mapplethorpe once said the statement grows out of what 
i do 
in 1979s easter lilies with mirror mapplethorpe uses four 
panels to form a cross around a center mirror the lilies are shown 
in dramatic shadows a dusting of light illuminating their inner 
and almost religious beauty it is a way of engaging the viewer 
beyond mere voyeurism the viewer becomes a part of the work 
but other works are disturbing unraveling a violent homosexual 
mystique for an unsuspecting audience they are terrifying 
sadomasochistic tableaux chained men leatherbound men men 
prepared for pain in an aristocratic setting anal sex games 
urination 
mapplethorpes defenders cite the first amendment which says 
that congress shall make no law abridging the freedom or 
speech or the press but courts have issued opinions back 
and forth since 1791 in 1957 the us supreme court gave its 
first ruling on a definition of obscenity saying it could not be 
protected by the first amendment 
justice william brennan however added the portrayal of sex 
eg in art literature and scientific works is not sufficient 
reason to deny material the constitutional protection of freedom of 
speech and press 
in 1973 the high court agreed to a new set of rules for states 
to determine what was obscene states could enact laws banning 
artistic works if they portrayed sex in a patently offensive way 
and which taken as a whole do not have serious literary artistic 
political or scientific value 
in june a us district court judge ruled that the rap group 2 
live crews lp as nasty as they wanna be which speaks 
graphically about sexual violence towards women was obscene 
