in a boston production of edward albees whos afraid of 
virginia woolf the character martha bellowed at her husband 
jesus christ youre trying to hump the hostess city censors 
forced the playwright to change the line because it took the 
lords name in vain said martha in the rewritten version mary 
magdalene youre trying to hump the hostess 
the muted nudity in the broadway smash hair was challenged 
in new york by a group of clergymen in 1968 
sister mary ignatius explains it all for you incurred the 
wrath of boston mayor raymond flynn when it ran there in 1984 
because it discussed abortion and homosexuality 
music too has had its romp with censors elvis the pelvis had 
to be shot from the waist up when he appeared on the ed sullivan 
show in 1956 so americans wouldnt be offended by those gyrating 
hips that helped make presley famous a decade later sullivan made 
the rolling stones change the lyrics to their song lets spend 
the night together they sang lets spend some time together 
instead 
in 1967 van morrison had a hit with browneyed girl which 
contained the line making love in the green grass an alternate 
version had to be made for objecting radio stations 
radio stations also demanded an alternate version to lloyd 
prices stagger lee in one two men have a fight playing cards 
and one shoots the other in the cleanedup version the men argue 
but patch it up and are sore no more 
jimi hendrix had to take the naked women off his electric 
ladyland lp about 20 years ago and in 1968 the stones were 
forced to part with the graffitifilled bathroom stall on beggars 
banquet lp 
