<TEXT>
but in no area has censorship so inflamed a passionate public as 
in literature 
according to the postmaster general of the united states in 
1959 lady chatterleys lover was an obscene and filthy 
work that could not be sent through the mail the ban was lifted 
a year later 
the post office burned 500 copies of ulysses in new york in 
1922 and the book considered a literary masterpiece was banned 
until 1933 the novel much of it written in stream of 
conciousness ripples with sex and sensuality 
and then i asked him with my eyes to ask again yes and 
then he asked me would i yes to say yes my mountain flower and 
first i put my arms around him yes and drew him down to me so he 
could feel my breasts all perfume yes and his heart was going like 
mad and yes i said yes i will yes 
henry millers tropic of cancer and all of his other works 
were banned in the united states until 1961 
theodore dreisers an american tragedy was kept off the 
shelves in massachusetts the diary of anne frank the wizard 
of oz and works by mark twain and stephen king have at one time 
or another been removed from libraries 
movies also have been a target 
as early as 1897 moralists railed against anything remotely 
suggesting sex some movie theater owners put white stripes across 
the screen when showing fatima a reel featuring a fully 
clothed dancer wiggling her hips and shaking her breasts 
there were censorship drives by clergymen to tell the public 
what they should and should not see and in 1922 hollywood decided 
to censor itself and made president hardings campaign manager 
will h hays the head of the motion picture producers and 
distributors of america he reigned for 25 years until the current 
ratings system came into being 
the hays office initially held up gone with the wind because 
of clark gables famous exit line frankly my dear i dont give 
a damn 
as late as 1953 otto premingers the moon is blue earned a 
production code ban for using such naughty words as virgin and 
mistress other terrible words appeared in anatomy of a 
murder such as contraception 
and in 1988 martin scorseses the last temptation of christ 
was called blasphemy by religious leaders 
more recently a rash of movies has earned the now defunct x 
rating including pedro almodovars tie me up tie me down 
filmmakers hope the new rating will carry none of the 
advertising and exhibition restraints of the x rating which had 
become synonymous with hardcore pornography and served no purpose 
