districts may abandon mandatory busing and other courtordered 
plans after achieving racial balance in student populations 
hundreds of school districts including those in most major 
cities operate courtordered desegregation plans only a few have 
persuaded courts to declare their oncesegregated systems fully 
integrated 
nevertheless the potential impact of the courts ruling is 
great critics say letting students attend neighborhood schools 
will result in resegregation 
the court will confront one aspect of the war on drugs when it 
reviews a michigan law that imposes mandatory life sentences 
without possibility of parole for people even firsttime 
offenders convicted of possessing certain amounts of drugs 
a man convicted of possessing 23 ounces of cocaine and given 
such a sentence says he received cruel and unusual punishment 
his lawyers note that convictions for seconddegree murder and 
other violent crimes do not carry such stiff sentences 
the justices were told that michigan is the only state that 
imposes such a mandatory sentence if the law is upheld other 
states might follow michigans lead 
here in summary form are some of the other cases the court is 
to decide this term 
