the taiwan government lifted restrictions 
thursday on the employment of foreign workers in government 
construction projects 
under the new rule approved by the cabinet contractors can 
apply for the importation of foreign workers for major government 
and special public projects 
currently they can only import up to onethird of the work 
force needed for such construction projects 
officials also said that all foreign workers should be protected 
by taiwans labor laws which stipulate that every worker receive a 
minimum monthly wage of 9750 taiwan dollars or about 357 us 
and be covered by health insurance 
the new move would help boost our economic development said 
chen chungsheng director general of occupational training bureau 
an agency under the labor council 
in 1985 the government announced 14 projects to be completed in 
the early 1990s including highway expansions a major rail line 
and rapid transit system for taipei chen said many of them have 
lagged behind schedule mainly because of the shortage of 
construction workers 
our workers dont like the nonskilled jobs that offer lower 
wages he explained 
earlier this month foreign minister fredrick chien urged the 
government to employ more workers from the philippines indonesia 
and thailand saying the three nations have showed strong interest 
in meeting taiwans labor regulations 
officials said at least 20000 foreigners mostly from southeast 
asia are working illegally in taiwan factories and construction 
