us merger activity picked up slightly during 
the third quarter from the previous three months but continued to 
fall back sharply from 1989 levels according to statistics 
released thursday 
the value of domestic mergers rose 7 percent from july through 
september when compared with the second quarter said securities 
data corp a business research firm 
during the third quarter there were 941 deals worth a total of 
586 billion announced against 1284 deals worth 478 billion 
announced in the second quarter the company said 
the pace was sharply lower from the 1231 transactions worth 
1394 billion announced in the third quarter of 1989 the 
yearearlier levels were already down sharply from 1988 when the 
takeover boom hit its peak 
the mergers business began to slow in early 1989 and then 
changed dramatically after last falls collapse of the junk bond 
market made financing for deals harder to come by 
in compiling its statistics securities data considered 
transactions including mergers acquisitions repurchases 
spinoffs selftenders of stock minority stake purchases and 
leveraged recapitalizations 
the number of stock repurchases increased during the third 
quarter as some companies took advantage of lower prices on wall 
street and began to buy back their shares 
the dow jones industrial average reached a high of 299975 on 
july 16 and 17 but has fallen more than 570 points since then as 
concerns about the economy and tensions in the persian gulf sent 
stock prices tumbling 
