union carbide corp announced thursday it 
would sell some assets and reorganize one of its principle 
subsidiaries under a restructuring plan expected to produce 600 
million in aftertax proceeds 
the plan calls for the danburybased company to sell up to half 
the equity in one subsidiary while selling off its interest in two 
businesses and restructuring its industrial gases business it also 
includes buying back up to 14 percent of its common stock 
about half of the 600 million in proceeds will be used to 
reduce the companys staggering debt which totaled 325 billion 
at the end of the second quarter said thomas f sprick spokesman 
for union carbide 
in trading thursday on the new york stock exchange union 
carbide stock closed up 62 cents at 1487 
one analyst said the plan was a step in the right direction but 
wouldnt change the fortunes of union carbide which suffered a 38 
percent decline in secondquarter earnings 
this is good but it could have been better it could have 
been a lot better said harvey s stober a chemical analyst with 
dean witter reynolds inc in new york they should joint venture 
their industrial gas corporation with a strong industrial gas 
producer in europe that is the jewel in this company 
under the plan union carbide would sell up to 50 percent of the 
equity in its ucar carbon company inc subsidiary a major supplier 
of carbon and graphite electrodes to the steel industry 
the sale is expected to result in a onetime aftertax book loss 
of up to 90 million said robert d kennedy carbides chairman 
and chief executive officer ucars sales last year totaled 802 
million 
the book loss from the ucar sale will be offset by an expected 
40 million profit from the sale of union carbides interest in two 
companies he said 
plans call for union carbide to sell off its 50 percent interest 
in kemet electronics corp which supplies capacitors and lincare 
inc a home oxygen and respiratory care supplier the company did 
not disclose the expected selling prices 
the restructuring also calls for union carbide to form five 
independent regional companies within its packaged gases 
subsidiary union carbide industrial gas company inc 
the companies will be formed after certain assets and businesses 
valued at approximately 55 million are divested kennedy said 
other businesses will also be added he said 
domestic sales of packaged gases last year totaled 300 million 
union carbide will also repurchase 20 million shares of common 
stock about 14 percent of its total common outstanding through a 
tender offer kennedy said 
an employee stock ownership plan is also part of the 
restructuring allowing workers to become majority owners of the 
new industrial gases companies kennedy said 
the employee stock ownership plan will be funded through an 
independently managed trust that will borrow 325 million to 
purchase shares of a new issue of convertible preferred stock from 
union carbide 
kennedy said the restructuring plan is designed to establish 
union carbide as a leading global chemical company focused on 
being the lowcost preferred supplier for its industries 
