hearing on the governments conflictofinterest allegations 
against him 
bush 35 was a director of silverado banking savings and loan 
association which collapsed in 1988 at an estimated cost to 
taxpayers of 1 billion 
the office of thrift supervision brought the action against 
bush which could lead to his being barred from the banking 
industry the ots alleges that bush failed to adequately inform 
fellow silverado directors of his business ties with developers 
kenneth good and bill walters who eventually defaulted on more 
than 132 million in silverado loans 
last week the federal deposit insurance corp sued bush and 
other former silverado directors for 200 million alleging that 
gross negligence on their part contributed to the sampls collapse 
bush told administrative law judge daniel j davidson he had 
absolutely no doubt his dealings with good and walters did not 
conflict with his role as a silverado director 
consequently bush said he did not consult with silverados 
management about the question of a potential conflict 
bush insisted several times that although good and walters 
invested in his oil company jnb exploration he had no financial 
interest in the projects for which they got loans from silverado 
previous testimony however showed that silverado extended a 
900000 line of credit to a partnership formed by bush and good to 
explore for oil and gas in argentina the line of credit intended 
to convince argentine officials that the venture had strong 
financial resources never was used 
under questioning from a government attorney bush said lawyers 
for goods company suggested that bush present the credit line 
proposal to silverados board 
i was a gobetween bush said 
bush maintained there was no conflict in his role because he 
didnt stand to gain any financial benefit from the credit line 
which he described as a sort of letter of referral and because 
he abstained from voting on the proposal 
pressed by ots attorney stephen hershkowitz however bush later 
admitted he had hoped the partnership would eventually benefit from 
the credit line since it would persuade the argentine government 
to permit the venture to drill wells in that country 
i didnt know if we would benefit i hoped that we would 
he said 
